### [Proverbs Chapter 18](../../../bib/kjv/pro018.htm#001.md)

[Proverbs 18:1](../../../bib/kjv/pro018.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_001">pro 18:1</span></span>

Desire - Thro' desire of wisdom, a man having separated himself from the
company, and noise, and business of the world, seeketh and intermeddleth
with all wisdom, uses all diligence, that he may search and find out all
solid knowledge and true wisdom.

[Proverbs 18:2](../../../bib/kjv/pro018.htm#002.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_002">pro 18:2</span></span>

Understanding - In getting sound and saving, knowledge. The discovery -
In uttering that folly and wickedness which is in his heart.

[Proverbs 18:3](../../../bib/kjv/pro018.htm#003.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_003">pro 18:3</span></span>

Cometh - Into any place or company. Contempt - He despiseth all
instruction and reproof. Reproach - And he shews his contempt by
ignominious and reproachful expressions.

[Proverbs 18:4](../../../bib/kjv/pro018.htm#004.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_004">pro 18:4</span></span>

A man's - A wise man's. As a brook - That wisdom which is in his heart
is continually pouring forth wise and good counsels.

[Proverbs 18:8](../../../bib/kjv/pro018.htm#008.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_008">pro 18:8</span></span>

They go - They wound mortally.

[Proverbs 18:9](../../../bib/kjv/pro018.htm#009.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_009">pro 18:9</span></span>

Is brother - Though they take several paths, yet both come to one end.

[Proverbs 18:10](../../../bib/kjv/pro018.htm#010.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_010">pro 18:10</span></span>

The name - The Lord, as he hath revealed himself in his works, and in
his word by his promises.

[Proverbs 18:14](../../../bib/kjv/pro018.htm#014.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_014">pro 18:14</span></span>

Sustain - Will easily support him under any outward troubles. Wounded -
Dejected with the sense of its own guilt and misery.

[Proverbs 18:18](../../../bib/kjv/pro018.htm#018.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_018">pro 18:18</span></span>

Parteth - Gives to every one what is right or meet.

[Proverbs 18:20](../../../bib/kjv/pro018.htm#020.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_020">pro 18:20</span></span>

Satisfied - Wise discourses tend to the satisfaction of the speaker, as
well as to the good of the hearers.

[Proverbs 18:21](../../../bib/kjv/pro018.htm#021.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_021">pro 18:21</span></span>

Death and life - Are brought upon men by, the good or bad use of their
tongues. Lovest - That love much talking.

[Proverbs 18:22](../../../bib/kjv/pro018.htm#022.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_022">pro 18:22</span></span>

A wise - A good wife; one that deserves the name, and performs the duty
of that relation. Favour - Obtains her not by his own diligence, but by
God's good providence.

[Proverbs 18:24](../../../bib/kjv/pro018.htm#024.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_024">pro 18:24</span></span>

A man - Heb. A man of friends; who desires the friendship of others.

